    <thetext>When using @AbstractRepositoryQueryPage2@ and creating dynamic controls, it might be required to reflow the SectionComposite once done to get proper scrollbars.

* createControl just creates the composite for the page
* setVisible dynamically creates the content of the composite
* needs ((SectionComposite) myComposite).getParent().getParent).reflow(true)

Though possible, I need to know about the internals and where in the hierarchy to find SectionComposite. I could potentially hold onto a reference myself when I get access in @createPageContent@.</thetext>
